title: Panic in <rustc_mir_build::build::expr::as_place::PlaceBuilder>::try_upvars_resolved

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
Hi there, First time the rust compiler crashes on me, here's a minimal example: ### Code ```Rust pub struct Example<'a, T> { a: T, b: &'a T, } impl<'a, T> Example<'a, T> { pub fn error_trying_to_destructure_self_in_closure(self) { let closure = || { let Self { a, b } = self; }; } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.66.0-nightly (432abd86f 2022-09-20) binary: rustc commit-hash: 432abd86f231c908f6df3cdd779e83f35084be90 commit-date: 2022-09-20 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.66.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'assertion failed: matches!(next(), Some(ProjectionElem :: Field(..)))', compiler/rustc_mir_build/src/build/expr/as_place.rs:250:17 error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.66.0-nightly (432abd86f 2022-09-20) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: --crate-type lib -C embed-bitcode=no -C debuginfo=2 -C incremental=[REDACTED] note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden query stack during panic: #0 [mir_built] building MIR for `::error_trying_to_destructure_self_in_closure::{closure#0}` #1 [unsafety_check_result] unsafety-checking `::error_trying_to_destructure_self_in_closure::{closure#0}` #2 [unsafety_check_result] unsafety-checking `::error_trying_to_destructure_self_in_closure` #3 [mir_const] processing MIR for `::error_trying_to_destructure_self_in_closure` #4 [mir_promoted] processing `::error_trying_to_destructure_self_in_closure` #5 [mir_borrowck] borrow-checking `::error_trying_to_destructure_self_in_closure` #6 [analysis] running analysis passes on this crate end of query stack ```
